50|$|Grazing {{incidence}} diffraction {{is used in}} X-ray spectroscopy and atom optics, where significant reflection can {{be achieved}} only at small values of the <b>grazing</b> <b>angle.</b> Ridged mirrors are designed for reflection of atoms coming at small <b>grazing</b> <b>angle.</b> This angle is usually measured in milliradians. In optics, there is Lloyd's mirror.|$|E
