50|$|Miller made {{numerous}} {{contributions in}} the area of special functions and addressed several significant open problems. Notable among these include his work with Emanuel Vegh in formulating an exact closed-form solution for the specular <b>grazing</b> <b>angle</b> for a sphere, a problem which had been unsolved for almost 50 years.|$|E
50|$|HF radars {{utilize the}} Bragg {{scattering}} mechanism and do always operate {{at very low}} <b>grazing</b> <b>angles.</b> Due to the low frequency of operation the radar waves are backscattered directly from the gravity waves and surface ripple need not be present.|$|R
